{
  "doc_id": "28511",
  "text": "NSAIDs are the most widely used pharmaceuticals for humans and animals due to their analgesic, antipyretic, and anti-inflammatory properties [CITATION_1] , and these compounds have been previously detected at high concentrations in treated wastewater from WWTPs [CITATION_2] . In the NSAID group, only flunixin, piroxicam, and indomethacin were detected in the snow samples. Other compounds of this group with high rates of use, such as carprofen, diclofenac, ibuprofen, and trimethoprim [CITATION_3] , were not detected in any sample. This phenomenon may be associated with the physicochemical properties of these substances.",
